cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on concurrency control in databases, specifically in the context of single writer multiple reader workloads. This suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is a likely category. The paper also discusses lock-free and wait-free algorithms, which are common topics in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of transactional memory and multiversion concurrency control suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) as another possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on optimizing for the common case rather than worst-case scenarios suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a potential category.
